Umbral shadow-archives near the Gloamvault site preserve observation records of Reliquary Host operations during the institution's late period — specifically the pattern of persons entering Host custody and the absence of records of their departure.
The Host's function as internal compliance enforcement is confirmed by Umbral records showing Host units operating in archive zones rather than perimeter zones during the period leading to the Night of Unsounded Bells.
The shift from external defense to internal suppression preceded the crisis by at least three years according to Umbral records, meaning the reassignment was institutional policy, not emergency improvisation.
This observation is relevant to the Reckoning faction's timeline analysis of when the Gloamvault's institutional capture became complete.
